This development comes in spite of 30 per cent of women in their twenties in Japan being underweight.

Base rent at the Lady Share House B&D is determined by multiplying the renter's weight in kilograms by 1,000 yen, in addition to a 38,000 yen floor price, according to the Japanese news website Otaku Kokka.

 

