The building has also opened an exercise studio equipped fitness equipments in order to help renters control and lose their weight. They also offer discounted beauty products, snacks and free lectures on weight management.

Mari Kataoka, the enterprise administrator, told Associated Press the original goal was to create a supportive environment for overweight women looking to lose weight, but has attracted women with 'normal' body shapes who wish to be incentivised to stay in shape, according to the Huffington Post.

