'Since the rent is lower if you lose weight, we thought overweight people would be coming to live here. Instead, we found that people who already have a great body come here and their goal is to maintain that physique,' she said.

Speaking of why the two-dozen tenants are provided with unlimited snacks and sugary soft drinks, Ms Kataoka said it was not a scam to increase rents.

She said: 'By having snacks at their disposal, we hope they will become more resistant to temptation. In this share house the residents have the same goals to lose weight, so it's easier not to give up.'

